The paper discusses a novel technique for improving the performance of counterfactual regret minimization (CFR) algorithm in solving two-player zero-sum extensive games with imperfect information. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including artificial intelligence (AI), game theory (GT), machine learning (LG), data structures (DS), and multi-agent systems (MA). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.DS, and cs.MA, in descending order of relevance.
